{
  "texts": [
    "We note also that the net-work's multi-branch and multi-scale integration could increase computational requirements and extend training durations, especially given its specialized application to graptolite fossil images, which are feature rich fossils.",
    "Lastly, Niu et al. (2024) present a DL-based approach for graptolite fossil identification.",
    "Utilizing a squeeze-and-excitation residual network (SE-Resnet50), the model outperforms human taxonomists in both accuracy and time efficiency.",
    "The novelty lies in the creation of the most extensive graptolite fossil dataset, annotated at the pixel level, combined with a cutting-edge deep learning model that incorporates TL.",
    "This research offers significant practical implications for enhancing geological surveys and shale gas exploration by reducing the time and cost of fossil identification."
  ]
}